\end{align}Then by Cauchy-Schwarz, \begin{align} &(a_n \cdot 6^n + a_{n - 1} \cdot 6^{n - 1} + \dots + a_1 \cdot 6 + a_0)(a_n \cdot 24^n + a_{n - 1} \cdot 24^{n - 1} + \dots + a_1 \cdot 24 + a_0) \\ &\ge (a_n \cdot 12^n + a_{n - 1} \cdot 12^{n - 1} + \dots + a_1 \cdot 12 + a_0)^2.
\end{align}In other words, $[f(12)]^2 \le 24 \cdot 1536 = 36864,$ so $f(12) \le 192.$ Equality occurs for $f(x) = \frac{x^3}{9},$ so the maximum value is $\boxed{192}.$
